  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "A 1.11 server returned a CRD validation error that does not correctly split up errors by fields with individual causes:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"kind\": \"Status\",\r\n  \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\r\n  \"metadata\": {},\r\n  \"status\": \"Failure\",\r\n  \"message\": \"ProwJob.prow.k8s.io \\\"origin-v4.0-20180916211224-e2e-aws\\\" is invalid: []: Invalid value: map[string]interface {}{\\\"spec\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"agent\\\":\\\"kubernetes\\\", \\\"job\\\":\\\"release-openshift-origin-installer-e2e-aws-master\\\", \\\"pod_spec\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"containers\\\":[]interface {}{map[string]interface {}{\\\"command\\\":[]interface {}{\\\"echo\\\", \\\"SUCCESS\\\"}, \\\"name\\\":\\\"echo\\\", \\\"resources\\\":map[string]interface {}{}}}}, \\\"report\\\":true, \\\"type\\\":\\\"periodic\\\"}, \\\"status\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"prev_report_state\\\":\\\"\\\", \\\"startTime\\\":interface {}(nil)}, \\\"apiVersion\\\":\\\"prow.k8s.io/v1\\\", \\\"kind\\\":\\\"ProwJob\\\", \\\"metadata\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"creationTimestamp\\\":\\\"2018-09-18T06:34:55Z\\\", \\\"generation\\\":1, \\\"uid\\\":\\\"f4facbd1-bb0c-11e8-aac3-42010a8e0004\\\", \\\"selfLink\\\":\\\"\\\", \\\"clusterName\\\":\\\"\\\", \\\"name\\\":\\\"origin-v4.0-20180916211224-e2e-aws\\\", \\\"namespace\\\":\\\"clayton-test-2\\\"}}: validation failure list:\\nmust validate at least one schema (anyOf)\\nmust not validate the schema (not)\",\r\n  \"reason\": \"Invalid\",\r\n  \"details\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"origin-v4.0-20180916211224-e2e-aws\",\r\n    \"group\": \"prow.k8s.io\",\r\n    \"kind\": \"ProwJob\",\r\n    \"causes\": [\r\n      {\r\n        \"reason\": \"FieldValueInvalid\",\r\n        \"message\": \"Invalid value: map[string]interface {}{\\\"kind\\\":\\\"ProwJob\\\", \\\"metadata\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"name\\\":\\\"origin-v4.0-20180916211224-e2e-aws\\\", \\\"namespace\\\":\\\"clayton-test-2\\\", \\\"creationTimestamp\\\":\\\"2018-09-18T06:34:55Z\\\", \\\"generation\\\":1, \\\"uid\\\":\\\"f4facbd1-bb0c-11e8-aac3-42010a8e0004\\\", \\\"selfLink\\\":\\\"\\\", \\\"clusterName\\\":\\\"\\\"}, \\\"spec\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"report\\\":true, \\\"type\\\":\\\"periodic\\\", \\\"agent\\\":\\\"kubernetes\\\", \\\"job\\\":\\\"release-openshift-origin-installer-e2e-aws-master\\\", \\\"pod_spec\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"containers\\\":[]interface {}{map[string]interface {}{\\\"name\\\":\\\"echo\\\", \\\"resources\\\":map[string]interface {}{}, \\\"command\\\":[]interface {}{\\\"echo\\\", \\\"SUCCESS\\\"}}}}}, \\\"status\\\":map[string]interface {}{\\\"prev_report_state\\\":\\\"\\\", \\\"startTime\\\":interface {}(nil)}, \\\"apiVersion\\\":\\\"prow.k8s.io/v1\\\"}: validation failure list:\\nmust validate at least one schema (anyOf)\\nmust not validate the schema (not)\",\r\n        \"field\": \"[]\"\r\n      }\r\n    ]\r\n  },\r\n  \"code\": 422\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `causes` array that kubectl and other clients use to display field specific errors is incorrect.  Each field should have its own `cause`, and the `field` should be a valid JSONPath pointer to the field (`status.state`).  \r\n\r\nThe summary message is also incorrect.\r\n\r\nIn general this made it almost impossible for me to debug why my object was incorrect, which is the entire point of the validation error type, so I consider this a serious usability blocker for CRD.  Validation needs to convey the field and a reasonably human readable message and be consistent with regular API object errors.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-api-machinery-bugs ",
